<dashboard version="1.1" theme="light">
  <label>top</label>
  <row>
    <panel>
      <html>
      <p>What: Returns the *most common value* of the field specified along with some statistics about that field</p>
      <p>How: <tt>... | top &lt;fieldname&gt;</tt>
        </p>
      <p>Why: Occasionally useful for reporting things, but often useful when you are exploring the data.</p>
      <p>So What: Quicker than doing your own <tt>stats</tt> to get these same statistics on a single field and how common it is.
        </p>
      <p>Docs: <a href="https://help.splunk.com/en/splunk-enterprise/search/spl-search-reference/10.0/search-commands/top">top</a>.
      </p>
      <p>See also <tt>rare</tt> which is the "reverse" of this command.</p>
      <p>Previous Command - <a href="tail">tail</a>
        </p>
      <p>Next Command - <a href="rare">rare</a>
        </p>
      </html>
    </panel>
    <panel>
      <html>
        <p>We're using data we built earlier by using <tt>outputlookup</tt>.  To build this see <a href="outputlookup">outputlookup</a>
        </p>
        <pre>| inputlookup rdf_cars.csv</pre>
        <p>While yours may differ slightly, that data for us is:</p>
      </html>
      <table>
        <search>
          <query>| inputlookup rdf_cars.csv</query>
        </search>
        <option name="count">12</option>
      </table>
    </panel>
  </row>
  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>Raw data</title>
      <html>
        This is the data
      </html>
      <table>
        <search>
          <query>| inputlookup rdf_cars.csv</query>
          <earliest>1708873200</earliest>
          <latest>1708959600</latest>
          <sampleRatio>1</sampleRatio>
        </search>
        <option name="count">12</option>
      </table>
    </panel>
    <panel>
      <title>Using top</title>
      <html>
        And here's the data with <tt>top "cars"</tt> applied.  "5" is the most common number so it's at the top.  Pun intended, please laugh now.
      </html>
      <table>
        <search>
          <query>| inputlookup rdf_cars.csv | top cars</query>
          <earliest>1708873200</earliest>
          <latest>1708959600</latest>
          <sampleRatio>1</sampleRatio>
        </search>
      </table>
    </panel>
  </row>
